  <entry>
    <title>The MIUI ROM</title>
    <link href="http://riteshk.github.com/blog/2011/07/26/the-miui-rom/"/>
    <updated>2011-07-26T22:54:00+01:00</updated>
    <id>http://riteshk.github.com/blog/2011/07/26/the-miui-rom</id>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Just installed the &lt;a href=&quot;http://miuiandroid.com/&quot;&gt;MIUI ROM&lt;/a&gt; on my Android
phone. I'd rooted my phone about 3 days after purchasing it and had been
running CyanogenMod 7. CyanogenMod is a nice, stable ROM for people who
want a no frills Android version which is closest to the stock Android
distribution with a few improvements. On the other hand, the MIUI ROM
contains lots of improvements over the stock distribution. The stock
Android interface has been given a complete overhaul with custom theme
elements that can be applied to almost every aspect of the UI
(notification area, lockscreen image etc).
My biggest gripe with CyanogenMod was the ADW launcher which would
randomly disappear at times after I'd unlocked the phone and swiped
somewhere on the homescreen. I believe this was a feature in ADW
launcher but it annoyed me to great lengths as I'd end up losing the
dialler application from the homescreen.
The MIUI ROM has an app launcher of its own that is probably &lt;del&gt;a ripoff&lt;/del&gt;
inspired by the iPhone with apps spread across multiple home screens.
This is quite convenient and I find it more intuitive compared to the
app drawer interface (ADW launcher/stock android launcher). A nice
feature is a backup application built right out of the box that can do
local and remote backups (I've not tested this entirely). The ROM also
detects an Apps2SD partition and moves applications to the SD card if
required. This is a huge plus for people who have phones with limited
internal memory and small /data partitions (e.g. the HTC Desire). I was
surprised to find that even with all UI effects, the phone is still very
responsive and seems to &lt;em&gt;feel&lt;/em&gt; faster.
The only minor issues I've faced so far are strange translation bugs
(the ROM is originally Chinese with an added English language pack) and
a missing weather application. The ROM is updated every Friday so the
translation bugs should be fixed very soon.
This is a really promising ROM that I hope to use for a long time.&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
