    <title>Installing rubygems in your home folder</title>
    <link href="http://riteshk.github.com/blog/2011/07/16/installing-rubygems-in-your-home-folder/"/>
    <updated>2011-07-16T00:00:00+01:00</updated>
    <id>http://riteshk.github.com/blog/2011/07/16/installing-rubygems-in-your-home-folder</id>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;No root? No problem! Obtain a copy of rubygems from ruby forge.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;$ tar xzvf rubygems-1.4.2 
$ cd rubygems-1.4.2 
$ ruby setup.rb --prefix=/your/home/folder/local 
$ echo &quot;RUBYLIB=$HOME:/same/path/as/above/lib&quot; &amp;gt;&amp;gt; ~/.bash_profile 
$ echo &quot;export RUBYLIB&quot; &amp;gt;&amp;gt; ~/.bash_profile 
$ source ~/.bash_profile
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should give you a working install of rubygems. Check out the environment&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;$ gem env 
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Install something&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;$ gem install rake 
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Enjoy!&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
